  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to see data (invisible) and notification (visible) payload passed through when app is backgrounded and you click on notification.\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\nSame as https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/1906 but for Android.\r\n\r\nAndroid appears to require setting click_action at the top level (this would be a change on status-go side too), and there seems to be some issues in setting notif and data payload concurrently.\r\n\r\n`react-native-fcm` documentation on how to handle this case:\r\n> When app is running in background (the tricky one, I strongly suggest you try it out yourself)\r\n\r\nand there's also an open issue with `question` label at https://github.com/evollu/react-native-fcm/issues/569 which isn't very encouraging, hence platform specific issue.\r\n\r\nRelated to https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/1883\r\n\r\nType: Feature\r\nPlatform: Android\r\n\r\n### Notes for testing\r\n\r\n1. Trigger a push notification by chatting with a contact with app in background\r\n2. Click on the notification\r\n3. Check logs and grep for `on-notification` - this should print something like \"hello1\" and \"ping\"",
